        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 6:32PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 632 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pickwick Dam, or near Pickwick Landing State Park, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pickwick Landing State Park, J P Coleman State Park, Walnut Grove,
Pickwick Dam, Pineflat, Shiloh, Counce, Lowryville, Damon, Southside,
Hamburg, Pollards Mill, Bruton Branch, Childers Hill, Winn Springs,
and Red Sulphur Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
